http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Man-arrested-for-circulating-counterfeit-notes/article14019857.ece

The city police have busted a counterfeit currency racket and arrested a 36-year-old person for trying to circulate counterfeit notes in the city.The arrested person, Shaukat Ahmed, is from Srinagar in Jammu and Kashmir. The police recovered 200 notes of Rs. 1,000 face value and 200 notes of Rs. 500 face value.Acting on a tip-off, police picked up Shaukat Ahmed when he was trying to circulate the notes at Krishna Rao Park. Investigations have now revealed that he used to frequent small shops, buy a low-cost product and hand over a Rs. 1,000 or Rs. 500 note.Police said that Shaukat claimed to have procured counterfeit notes from Bangladesh through middlemen. A senior officer said that Shaukat is the last man in the chain and they are trying to uncover the gang behind the racket.